&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Candidate Experience Coordinator at Databricks, you&#39;ll be the engine that powers our recruiting efforts, scheduling interviews, and moving candidates through the pipeline. As one of the first points of contact for candidates, you&#39;ll partner with Recruiters, Sourcers, and hiring teams to deliver an exceptional interviewing experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build relationships and trust with the broader Talent Acquisition team, cross-functional partners, and hiring stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate high volumes of virtual and in-person interviews by navigating complex scheduling scenarios across multiple stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for candidates, managing timely, professional, and friendly communication (written and verbal) to ensure candidates feel supported throughout their journey&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle candidate travel arrangements and expenses for in-person interviewing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executing other post-interviewing tasks such as scheduling debriefs and reference checks, and generating offer letters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to and identify data-driven improvements and ad hoc projects that enhance our recruitment processes and candidate experience programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we&#39;re looking for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C1/C2 English proficiency&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and prioritization skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment with evolving needs&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset and openness to feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive approach to resolving ambiguous challenges&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of high accuracy and attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An interest in technology and artificial intelligence&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Databricks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Databricks is the data and AI company. More than 10,000 organizations worldwide — including Comcast, Condé Nast, Grammarly, and over 50% of the Fortune 500 — rely on the Databricks Data Intelligence Platform to unify and democratize data, analytics and AI. Databricks is headquartered in San Francisco, with offices around the globe and was founded by the original creators of Lakehouse, Apache Spark™, Delta Lake and MLflow. To learn more, follow Databricks on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot;&gt;&lt;a style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot; href=&quot;https://twitter.com/databricks&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://twitter.com/databricks&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1700237575733000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw03FL8fJvOD97ytN02f5G2C&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot; href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/databricks&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.linkedin.com/company/databricks&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1700237575733000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw15dLk3q8VxTfHEgCUg7NSt&quot;&gt;LinkedIn&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot; href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/databricksinc&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.facebook.com/databricksinc&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1700237575733000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw39EcncitnlqV72EG2-RqXJ&quot;&gt;Facebook&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt

&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;GAQ426R358&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;1648&quot;&gt;While candidates in the listed location(s) are encouraged for this role, candidates in other locations will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Chief of Staff to the Chief People Officer (CPO) to help drive operational excellence, strategic alignment, and execution across the Databricks People organization. In this role, you will work closely with the CPO and People Leadership Team to ensure that our strategy, priorities, and operating rhythms are aligned and effectively executed as we scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will play a critical role in connecting strategy to execution, enabling strong collaboration across the People Leadership Team and Centers of Excellence, and ensuring the CPO’s time and focus are directed toward the most impactful priorities for the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A key part of this role will be helping support the transformation of the People organization into an AI-first, highly efficient function, identifying opportunities to leverage AI to automate routine work, accelerate insights, improve decision-making, and fundamentally change how the People team operates at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;2006&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;The impact you will have: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the operating cadence of the People Leadership Team, including leadership meetings, quarterly and annual planning, and strategic reviews.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure alignment across People functions and Centers of Excellence by linking strategy, planning, and execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with functional leaders, PMO and finance to translate company priorities into clear People team objectives and operational plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop reporting mechanisms and dashboards to track key People metrics, strategic initiatives, and organizational performance, and coordinate reporting metrics to the board and executive team as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement AI-powered tools and workflows to improve the operating efficiency of the People organization, from automating routine reporting and communications to accelerating how the team synthesizes data and gets to better decisions, faster.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;2367&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-renderer-mark=&quot;true&quot;&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a Chief of Staff, Strategy Lead, or similar role supporting a senior executive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–12+ years of experience in HR, strategy, operations, consulting, or business operations. Experience working with People/HR organizations or talent strategy initiatives is strongly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong strategic thinking and program management skills with the ability to translate strategy into operational execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional organizational and communication skills with experience supporting senior executives and working effectively across cross-functional stakeholders to drive results across complex organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage cross-functional initiatives across complex organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and data storytelling skills to drive insight and decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate effectively in a high-growth, fast-paced environment and drive alignment through ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine AI adopter who actively uses AI tools to do their own work better, and brings curiosity and initiative to identifying how these tools can transform how the People team operates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Range Tran

&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;SLSQ427R2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;2729&quot;&gt;Want to help solve the world’s toughest problems with data and AI? This is what we do every day at Databricks.&lt;br&gt;Databricks operates at the leading edge of the Data and AI space. Our customers turn to us to lead the accelerated innovation their businesses need to gain first-mover advantage in today’s ultra-competitive landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;As a Core Account Executive (Digital Natives) at Databricks, you will own a focused territory of ~10 large Digital Native spending accounts across the Nordics. As a successful candidate, you are a high-achieving sales professional and self-starter who understands the consumption sales process. You know how to sell innovation and value to existing customers, are always prospectng and identifying new use cases and growing consumption, and can guide deals forward to compress decision cycles. You love understanding a product in-depth, and are passionate about communicating its value to customers and partners.&amp;nbsp;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;You will report to the Senior Manager, Emerging Enterprise Nordics. This role is based in Stockholm, though we are open to strong candidates located in other parts of Sweden.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The impact you will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess your territory and develop a successful execution strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive quarter-on-quarter consumption growth in existing accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceed activity and quarterly revenue targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track all customer details including use case, purchase time frames, next steps, and forecasting in Salesforce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify new use case opportunities and showcase value to existing customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote the value of the Databricks&#39; Data Intelligence Platform and other products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure 100% satisfaction among all customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of the data platform and cloud ecosystems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some exposure to the software industry and understanding of selling SaaS, Data and Business Value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience growing consumption and closing commit deals in a direct sales role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competent with prospecting research and ability to map out key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced understanding of MEDDPICC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience exceeding sales targets/quotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree or relevant work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Databricks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Databricks is the data and AI company. More than 10,000 organizations worldwide — including Comcast, Condé Nast, Grammarly, and over 50% of the Fortune 500 — rely on the Databricks Data Intelligence Platform to unify and democratize data, analytics and AI. Databricks is headquartered in San Francisco, with offices around the globe and was founded by the original creators of Lakehouse, Apache Spark™, Delta Lake and MLflow. To learn more, follow Databricks on&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot;&gt;&lt;a style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot; href=&quot;https://twitter.com/databricks&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://twitter.com/databricks&amp;amp;source=gmail&amp;amp;ust=1700237575733000&amp;amp;usg=AOvVaw03FL8fJvOD97ytN02f5G2C&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a style=&quot;color: rgb(255, 54, 33);&quot; href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/company/databricks&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-saferedirecturl=&quot;https://www.goo

&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;SLSQ227R43&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Databricks, we’re on a mission to help organisations use data and AI to solve the world’s toughest problems — and few opportunities are more rewarding than driving positive change across New South Wales Public Sector. We’re looking for a passionate and results-driven Enterprise Account Executive to help our government partners harness the full power of the Databricks platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a pioneering sales role within our Public Sector Sales team, reporting directly to the Senior Sales Director. You’ll work at the forefront of digital transformation in the Public Sector space, helping agencies reimagine how they deliver outcomes and play a pivotal role in shaping Databricks’ presence across the country. As a successful candidate, you are a creative, energetic self-starter who understands the sales process. You know how to sell innovation and change through customer vision expansion and can drive deals forward to compress decision cycles. You love understanding a product in depth and are passionate about communicating its value to Customers and System Integrators. Always hunting for new opportunities, you will be asked to close net new accounts while maintaining existing accounts. Along with the chance to close an exciting deal, we also offer accelerators above 100% quota accomplishment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Impact You Will Have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving Consumption: Help customers derive value from the platform by identifying key use cases and increasing usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion real-world change: Lead initiatives that make measurable impact — from accelerating innovation in health and education to supporting sustainability and economic development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape Databricks’ Public Sector footprint: Identify, structure, and close strategic opportunities that align our capabilities with Australia’s digital priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire through connection: Build trusted relationships with senior decision-makers, tell compelling stories about our impact, and influence at the highest levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute with excellence: Manage the end-to-end sales cycle — from prospecting and initial engagement to closing transformative deals and driving platform adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate for success: Work with solution architects, customer success, and global teams to deliver solutions that empower customers and ensure long-term success.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What We Look For:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for impact — you’re motivated by helping organisations use technology for the public good.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in enterprise or Public Sector sales, ideally in Cloud, Data, or SaaS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic and structured in approach, with strong execution and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and relationship-building skills with senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growth mindset, creativity, and adaptability in dynamic, innovative environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Spark and Big Data is highly desirable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Databricks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
